A buyer's Guide to Marketing SolutionsMarketing Software Buyer’s Guide
 
If revenue directly comes from sales, sales, on the other hand, is the direct result of marketing. Maybe not all will agree on this premise but all would probably say yes when asked by this question: Are sales and marketing important elements of your business? Next to ROI, marketing conversion rate will more likely be the main focus of a well-versed modern-day internet marketer. Marketing is communicating the value of a product or service to a customer with the goal in mind of selling that same product or service. This is not an easy job most especially when significant type and volume of products are involve. But thanks to the marketing software, it makes our life easier, faster and our business, profitable.
 
Through this Buyer’s Guide, we at ITQlick.com would like you to re-examine your current position in marketing and further encourage you to discover the value and impact of marketing software solution on your overall performance. We all know it. Marketing is the life and blood of business. There is more to learn on this scientific body knowledge and one of them is the acquisition process of the right marketing software solution for your business.
 
Types
Marketing software solutions are here for these two important tasks: 1) conduct customer/market segmentation and 2) campaign development and management. With this principle in mind, marketing leads us into these three major types of marketing solutions.
 
Marketing Intelligence
By tracking the customers’ response on marketing campaigns conducted via different channels, marketing software solution is able to gather and measure data from these activities. This helps marketer in developing better programs and campaigns that can boost market conversion rate.
 
Marketing Automation
With the primary focus of converting leads into customers, marketing automation automates marketing processes including customer segmentation, customer data integration, and campaign management.
 
Advanced Workflow Automation
With the primary objective of increasing the marketer's ability to deliver relevant content to relevant individuals at relevant times, workflow automation focuses more on streamlining the internal marketing processes of an organization.
 
It is clear that these sets of technology help marketers manage the customer experience across different marketing channels. In a broader sense, marketing software solutions are there to provide strategic process automation. Marketing software products help marketers in:
 


		developing and implementing email marketing campaigns

		automating repetitive business tasks

		creating and managing a central database for present and potential customers

		integrating processes and activities in Customer Relationship Management (CRM) system

		developing automated campaigns and programs to increase the overall business sales

 
Features
Most marketing software solutions rooted out from Customer Relationship Management (CRM) and Email Marketing industries. Let’s go over with this list of features that will help you better understand the power of available marketing software solutions today.
 
Database
Database supports every feature and function of a marketing platform. It is where contact data and activity histories for each lead and customer are saved and secured.
 
Email Marketing Engine
Considered as the hardest working marketing tool, automated email campaigns can produce conversion rates two times higher than non-automated ones.
 
Automated Programs
Lead nurturing programs like series of follow-up messages and scheduled call-to-action alerts helps improve lead-to-customer conversion process.
 
Lead Scoring
This involves the assigning of score or value to the activity and demographic data of the lead who visited a certain store or website. This help marketers in analyzing the buying cycle of a lead and come with actions or solutions that help convert them to buyers.
 
Landing Pages
This is the web page where you intend to bring your prospect leads after clicking a link, button or text in an email or blog as a result of a call-to-action campaign.
 
Forms and Surveys
Forms and surveys are powerful engagement tools. Automating the sending, processing of data, and generating of report out of these forms and surveys help companies in a variety of ways.
 
Website Visitor Tracking
Web Analytics and the popular Google Analytics help analyze web traffic. Number of visitors, their activity on the site, and their demographic profile when analyze results to formulation of better marketing campaigns.
 
CRM Integration
Integrating your marketing automation database with CRM systems like Salesforce, Microsoft Dynamics, and Sugar CRM helps you in understanding better your leads and customers. CRM connects the dots between marketing, sales and customer service.
 
Web Event Integration
Web events like webinars require a lot of efforts to organize. Integrating such activity into your marketing software helps you save time and even allows you reach a greater number of participants.
 
Social Marketing
Social media marketing can be automated. Auto-post, auto-tweet, and auto-respond features are now all possible to be incorporated in your social media campaigns.
 
Analytics and Reports
With real-time reports, your time to make sound decision relevant to your next marketing strategy can be maximized. Going deeper with the analytics features, like the dashboard, your marketing solution can help you analyze better the bigger picture of the market where you are operating.
 
In addition, don’t forget to check the common features like ease of use, overall speed performance, and availability of training and support, and mobility features.
 
Solutions per Business Size, per Vendor
Marketing software solutions are available from a wide range of vendors. They are segmented into three major levels: Enterprise Players, Small and Medium Business Players, Niche Providers. Solution providers, industry analysts, consultants and software users agree the these segments were formed by carefully considering these parameters:
 


		Target industry

		Features included

		Focus or scope covered

		Degree of integration

		Ease-of-use and internal resources available

		Efficiency of internal processes and relevance of designed flows

		Content and relevant offers

 
Eloqua and Marketo are both enterprise players that offer a variety of functions on the solutions they provide. Aprimo, Unica, Teradata and SAS Institute are also among of the top performers in this market segment.
 
In the SMB market is where many players are thriving and competing against each other in providing the best-of-breed (industry-specific) and hybrid (or CRM that includes marketing functions) solutions. Salesforce.com, SAP and Microsoft all offers solutions that can be integrated with another vendor’s technology tools.
 
Neolane, Exact Target and Silverpop are niche players. They are also known as specialist marketing automation vendors. Most of these specialists are providing marketing solutions to the B2C and B2B consumer markets.
 
